\begin{abstract}
This note summarizes a baseline run on the public challenge CSV: signal/background labels (\texttt{s}/\texttt{b}), event weights, missing values encoded as \(-999\) (treated as NaN in the model), weighted \textbf{signal vs.\ background} distributions in collinear mass \(m_{\mathrm{MMC}}\), and \textbf{approximate median significance} (AMS) summarized from stratified K-fold cross-validation on the training table (mean$\pm$std over folds).
Leaderboard scores on the held-out \texttt{KaggleSet} test rows are \emph{not} reproduced here.
\end{abstract}

